Package CallOf2D

package CallOf2D
  • Class
    Description
    Asset
    Asset class is a superclass that is used by every entity in the game.
    AssetController
    AssetController class is one of the most important classes in the program.
    Bullet
    Bullet class is used to create new bullet objects.
    Camera
    Camera class is a class that helps translate the assets in the game, making it appear as though the camera is following the player
    Enemy
    Enemy class is used to create new enemy objects.
    Floor
    Floor class is used to add floors into the game.
    Game
    Game class is the main class for our game! It is the file you need to run for the game to work.
    ID
    Enum ID created for the assets in the game to have an ID that will determine how they interact with each other.
    ImageLoader
    ImageLoader class loads images from a PNG file.
    KeyInput
    KeyInput class is created to "listen" to the keyboard and receive inputs from the user.
    MedKit
    MedKit class to allow player to pick up med kits to heal themselves for 40 health.
    Player
    Player class is the class created to add the player into the game.
    Sound
    Sound class enables us to create music and sound effects for our game through Java's imported libraries.
    SpeedUp
    SpeedUp class to create speed boost powerups to increase the player's speed
    Wall
    Wall class is the class created to add walls into the game.
    Window
    The Window class implements Java AWT and Java Swing to create a window
